   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CDD</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CDD has been a key player in Bangladesh and many other developing countries for integrating disability into development initiatives. This partnership will utilise the skills and capacities to strengthen the existing structures and systems of national and local government and to explore endorsement of capacity enhancement initiatives through CBR training module.

Goal: Strengthening System for a Disability Inclusive Development Process in Bangladesh 
Purpose of Project: Persons with disabilities are increasingly participating in the society and the quality of their lives improved in Bangladesh through sustainable system development. The project aims to develop and strengthen capacities by developing standard tools, guidelines, manuals, IEC materials to support the national effort to mainstream disability. It focuses on facilitating the process of GO-NGO &amp; Private Sector Human Resources Development on social inclusion and explore possible areas of collaboration with academic institutes</narrative>
  </description>
